First, the Yellow Taxi data from August2019 and December2019 data is combined:

yellowTaxi <- rbind( read.csv("yellow_tripdata_2019-08.csv"),
                read.csv("yellow_tripdata_2019-12.csv"))

Then,the Green Taxi data is combined:

greenTaxi <- rbind( read.csv("green_tripdata_2019-08.csv"),
                read.csv("green_tripdata_2019-12.csv"))

Now, the trip duration will be calculated

yellowTaxi$tripduration <- as.duration(interval(yellowTaxi$tpep_pickup_datetime,yellowTaxi$tpep_dropoff_datetime)) 
greenTaxi$tripduration <- as.duration( interval(greenTaxi$lpep_pickup_datetime, greenTaxi$lpep_dropoff_datetime))

Next, PickUp DateTime and DropOff DateTime will be separated into PickUp Date/DropOff Date and PickUp time/DropOff Time

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% separate(tpep_pickup_datetime, c("pickup.date", "pickup.time"), " ")
yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% separate(tpep_dropoff_datetime, c("dropoff.date", "dropoff.time"), " ")
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% separate(lpep_pickup_datetime, c("pickup.date", "pickup.time"), " ")
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% separate(lpep_dropoff_datetime, c("dropoff.date", "dropoff.time"), " ")

Now, the data will be clean a bit: First, omitting all NA values

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% na.omit()
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi[-17] #elimnates a row full of NAs
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% na.omit()

We will only use the data of trips that lasted more than 5 minutes:

yellowTaxi <-yellowTaxi%>% filter( tripduration >= 300 )
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% filter(tripduration >= 300)

Also, for Rate Code ID we only need to see the values from 1-6:

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% filter( RatecodeID >= 1 & RatecodeID <= 6 )
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% filter( RatecodeID >=1 & RatecodeID <=6)

We need to filter tip amount, since no one can get -100 as tip:

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% filter(tip_amount >=0 & tip_amount <=50)
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% filter(tip_amount >=0 & tip_amount<=50)

More filtering: -trip distance:

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>%filter(trip_distance >=0 & trip_distance <=22)
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% filter(trip_distance >=0 & trip_distance <=15)

-fare amount

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% filter(fare_amount >=0 & fare_amount <=100)
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% filter(fare_amount >=0 & fare_amount <=100)

-extra

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% filter(extra >=0 )
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% filter(extra >=0 )

-MTA tax

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% filter(mta_tax >=0 )
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% filter(mta_tax >=0 )

-tolls amount

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% filter(tolls_amount >=0 )
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% filter(tolls_amount >=0 )

-total amount

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% filter(total_amount >=0 & total_amount <=200)
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% filter(total_amount >=0 & total_amount <=200)

Since payment_type is a numeric value, it will change to a character value following this rule: - 1 = Credit card - 2 = Cash - 3 = No charge - 4 = Dispute - 5 = Unknown - 6 = Voided Trip

payment<- function(a){
  if(a == 1){
    return( "Credit Card" )
  }
  
  if(a== 2){
    return( "Cash" )
  }
  
  if(a == 3){
    return( "No Charge" )
  }
  
  if(a == 4){
    return( "Dispute" )
  }
  
  if(a == 5){
    return( "Unknown" )
  }
  
  if(a == 6){
    return( "Voided Trip" )
  }
}

Now, payment_type is change:

yellowTaxi$payment_type <- sapply(yellowTaxi$payment_type, payment)
greenTaxi$payment_type <- sapply(greenTaxi$payment_type, payment)

plotting trip type: First, the variable needs to be changed from numerical to character: - 1 = Street-hail - 2 = Dispatch

tripType <- function(t){
  if(t == 1){
    return( "Street-hail")
    }
  if(t == 2){
    return("Dispatch")
    }
}
greenTaxi$trip_type <- sapply(greenTaxi$trip_type, tripType)
ggplot(greenTaxi, aes(x= trip_type))+ 
         geom_bar(stat = "count", width = 0.80, na.rm = T, fill= "green" ) + labs( title = "Trip Type- Green Taxis", x = "Type", y= "")

plotting vendedorID: - 1 = Creative Mobile Technologies, LLC - 2 = VeriFone Inc.

id <- function(i){
  if(i==1){
    i="LLC"
  }
  else if(i==2){
    i="VeriFone"
  }
  else{
    i="--"
  }
}
greenTaxi$VendorID <- sapply(greenTaxi$VendorID, id )
yellowTaxi$VendorID <- sapply(yellowTaxi$VendorID, id)

plots:

ggplot(yellowTaxi, aes(x= VendorID))+

rate code id: - 1 = standard rate - 2 = JFK - 3 = Newark - 4 = Nassau or Westchester - 5 = Negotiated fare - 6 = Group ride

rateCode <- function(r){
  if( r==1){
    return("Standard rate")
  }
  if( r== 2){
    return("JFK")
  }
  if( r==3 ){
    return("Newark")
  }
  if( r==4 ){
    return("Nassau/Westchester")
  }
  if( r== 5 ){
    return("Negotiated fare")
  }
  if( r==6 ){
    return("Group ride")
  }
}
yellowTaxi$RatecodeID <- sapply(yellowTaxi$RatecodeID, rateCode )
greenTaxi$RatecodeID <- sapply(greenTaxi$RatecodeID, rateCode )
ggplot(greenTaxi, aes(x= RatecodeID))+ 
         geom_bar(stat = "count", width = 0.80, na.rm = T, fill= "green" ) + labs( title = "Rate code- Green Taxis", x = " ", y= "")

ggplot(yellowTaxi, aes(x= RatecodeID))+ 
         geom_bar(stat = "count", width = 0.80, na.rm = T, fill= "yellow" ) + labs( title = "Rate code- Yellow Taxis", x = " ", y= "")

Since data from August and December is being used, both data will be compared. First, the Start Date is divided by year, month, and day

yellowTaxi <- yellowTaxi%>% separate(pickup.date, c("year", "month", "day"), "-")
greenTaxi <- greenTaxi%>% separate(pickup.date, c("year", "month","day"), "-")

The data is filtered and put into separate data frames.

augYellow <- filter(yellowTaxi, month== '08')

decYellow <- filter(yellowTaxi, month== '12')
augGreen <- filter(greenTaxi, month== '08')
decGreen <- filter(greenTaxi, month=='12')
